	<!-- custom: we have modified this in AdvCiv-SAS, now walls and castles stay relevant even at renaissance and after, no reason to prevent that, seems more intuitive to me as walls are still a component of later eras up to modern times, and something that could be used to shield against an attacker if i am not mistaken, at least i want it to be this way in AdvCiv-SAS, may help nerf the op gun units, that will be op if needed in other ways but not by melting through walls like it's butter if i may say anyways etc anyways etc anyways etc... See also <bIgnoreBuildingDefense>0</bIgnoreBuildingDefense> in CIV4UnitInfos.xml (for details anyways etc) or/and (tranlslate to english ((following) web page (anyways etc)) using web browser or such) https://gforestshade.github.io/kujira/post/civ4unitinfos/#bignorebuildingdefense for details. -->
	<!-- advc.004c: Based on TXT_KEY_BUILDING_DEFENSE_MOD (see below).
		 For the DefenseRaise XML tag. Use the defense icon and refer to
		 non-gunpowder-based units as "pre-Renaissance". "Gunpowder-based" is
		 too similar to "Gunpowder" (unit class). -->
	<TEXT>
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_DEFENSE_RAISE</Tag>
		<English>[ICON_BULLET]Raises [ICON_DEFENSE] to %d1_Mod%% against All Units (using now bIgnoreBuildingDefense 0 ... for all units... right?(?))</English>
	</TEXT>
	<!-- custom: about the ones below ("_DEFENSE_MOD", "_BUILDING_BOMBARD_DEFENSE"), i am not sure it is covered by <bIgnoreBuildingDefense>0</bIgnoreBuildingDefense> but updating the text as well because it is how i would want it to be ideally, hopefully clearer this way despite my confusion, ideally it works as intended, else the issue is raised at least maybe or not, but anyways etc anyways etc anyways etc... todo investigate this more if need(ed(?)) anyways etc anyways etc anyways etc... -->
	<!-- DEFENSE_MOD should be supplanted by DEFENSE_RAISE. But perhaps it
		 won't be in a mod-mod. So let's update DEFENSE_MOD as well: Use the
		 defense icon and state that it increases (only) building defense. -->
	<TEXT> <!-- redefine -->
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_DEFENSE_MOD</Tag>
		<English>[ICON_BULLET]+%d1_Mod%% Building [ICON_DEFENSE] (against pre-Renaissance Units (only?(?)))</English>
	</TEXT>
	<!-- From CIV4GameText_Warlords_Changed.xml.
		 To be consistent with the above. -->
	<TEXT> <!-- redefine -->
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BOMBARD_DEFENSE_MOD</Tag>
		<English>[ICON_BULLET]%D1_Mod%% [ICON_DEFENSE] Bombardment (by pre-Renaissance Units only?(?))</English>
	</TEXT>
	<!-- From CIV4GameTextInfos.xml. Also for consistency. Chichen Itza
		 actually is cumulative with culture defense. -->
	<TEXT> <!-- redefine -->
		<Tag>TXT_KEY_BUILDING_DEFENSE_MOD_ALL_CITIES</Tag>
		<English>[ICON_BULLET]%d1_Mod%% [ICON_DEFENSE] in All Cities</English>
	</TEXT>


	<!-- custom: do not rename the tag itself as we would have to recompile
	and may break compatibility with other mods, we mostly (just or not)
	wanted to rename the tag of promotioninfo itself that is much more used
	and prone to confusing those who read it maybe, at least me, anyways.
	We may also have to change it in a lot more places that we would want
	to or need to, for other promotions with a similar case of renaming.
	
	So focus mostly/only on the most import change, which is here is to add
	"Air" explicitly in the text to clarify	it is about air units, may or not
	do similarly for such other or similar or not texts.
	-->
	<TEXT>
